text.KPI name and description:
Non-Cheque Performance: Collection and delivery punctuality excluding cheque run;
i) Business Critical
ii) Business Flexible

Value for Money. VfM reported as part of quarterly and annual narrative reporting, with evidence of how VfM considerations have informed decisions relating to resource allocation and improving efficiency. Percentage of KPI is measured by taking in consideration supplier’s achievement in quarterly scoring system done by FCDO: 
   5: Outstanding Performance. Consistently to a higher than required standard. No fee deduction; 
   4: Exceeding Performance. Consistently to the required standard but above this at least once. No fee deduction;
   3: Satisfactory Performance. Consistently to the required standard. No fee deduction;
   2: Less than Satisfactory Performance. Generally to the required standard, but below what is expected at least once. Deduction of 50% of fees;
   1: Serious Underperformance. Consistently below the expected standard. Deduction of 100% of fees.

text.Good target:
Severity 1 & 2 -100%; 
Severity 3 & 4 - 95%; 
Success of all other Change Categories - 100%
